      100%;">Alpheios</span></a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><div
      style="text-align: left;"><img
      alt="http://alpheios.net/sites/all/themes/alpheiostheme/logo.png"
      src="http://alpheios.net/sites/all/themes/alpheiostheme/logo.png" /><span
      style="font-size: 100%;"> </span><span style="font-size:
      85%;">&nbsp;</span></div></blockquote><blockquote
      class="tr_bq"><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size: x-small;">The
      goal of the Alpheios project is to help people learn how to learn languages as efficiently and
      enjoyably as possible, and in a way that best helps them understand their own literary heritage
      and culture, and the literary heritage and culture of other peoples throughout
      history.</span>
      </blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Our initial focus will be on classical literature in languages
      no longer spoken, such as Latin and ancient Greek. The influence of these classics, like the
      river Alpheios, still runs like a subterranean stream deep beneath the contemporary world, as
      artists and thinkers continue to draw inspiration from them.</span>
      </blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">We hope that Alpheios will eventually include a wide variety of
      languages, ancient and modern. By utilizing contemporary technology that is both flexible and
      adaptive, Alpheios should make language learning both easier and more immediately rewarding. By
      sharing these tools and the source code in which they are written freely on the Web, the
      Alpheios Project also hopes to encourage their collaborative development.</span>
      </blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">The software is currently in Beta release, with all the caveats
      normally associated with that level of
      development.</span></blockquote><h3><span style="font-size:
